<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-05-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-05-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="632" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d632">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Muruaga</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-05-19"><hi rend="italic">May 19,
                                1894</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge receipt of
                            your note of 14th instant, making inquiries touching changes in the
                            duties at present operative under the reciprocity arrangement.</p>
                        <p>A copy of your note has been laid before the Secretary of the Treasury
                            for his consideration and an expression of his views upon the
                            subject-matter thereof.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary</hi>,</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>